        <codeph class="+ topic/ph pr-d/codeph " xtrf="file:/Volumes/Matt_files/Git/mb/markdown-validator/docs-user/user-guide/tasks/t_set-output-format.dita" xtrc="codeph:4;49:17">--format json</codeph>.</cmd>
        <info class="- topic/itemgroup task/info " xtrf="file:/Volumes/Matt_files/Git/mb/markdown-validator/docs-user/user-guide/tasks/t_set-output-format.dita" xtrc="info:2;50:15">
          <codeblock xml:space="preserve" class="+ topic/pre pr-d/codeblock " xtrf="file:/Volumes/Matt_files/Git/mb/markdown-validator/docs-user/user-guide/tasks/t_set-output-format.dita" xtrc="codeblock:3;51:43">md-validate validate docs/article.md --rules rules/tutorial.json --format json</codeblock>
          <p class="- topic/p " xtrf="file:/Volumes/Matt_files/Git/mb/markdown-validator/docs-user/user-guide/tasks/t_set-output-format.dita" xtrc="p:2;52:14">The JSON output includes all rule results and metadata:</p>
          <codeblock xml:space="preserve" class="+ topic/pre pr-d/codeblock " xtrf="file:/Volumes/Matt_files/Git/mb/markdown-validator/docs-user/user-guide/tasks/t_set-output-format.dita" xtrc="codeblock:4;53:43">{
  "filepath": "docs/article.md",
  "score": 5,
  "total_rules": 6,
  "passed": false,
  "results": [
    {"rule_id": 1, "rule_name": "topic-must-be-tutorial", "passed": true, ...},
    {"rule_id": 4, "rule_name": "description-must-exist",  "passed": false,
     "mitigation": "Add a description field to the front matter.", ...}
  ]
}</codeblock>
        </info>
      </step>

      <step id="step-csv" class="- topic/li task/step " xtrf="file:/Volumes/Matt_files/Git/mb/markdown-validator/docs-user/user-guide/tasks/t_set-output-format.dita" xtrc="step:3;67:27">
        <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd " xtrf="file:/Volumes/Matt_files/Git/mb/markdown-validator/docs-user/user-guide/tasks/t_set-output-format.dita" xtrc="cmd:3;68:14">To produce CSV output for spreadsheet analysis, add
        <codeph class="+ topic/ph pr-d/codeph " xtrf="file:/Volumes/Matt_files/Git/mb/markdown-validator/docs-user/user-guide/tasks/t_set-output-format.dita" xtrc="codeph:5;69:17">--format csv</codeph>.</cmd>
        <info class="- topic/itemgroup task/info " xtrf="file:/Volumes/Matt_files/Git/mb/markdown-validator/docs-user/user-guide/tasks/t_set-output-format.dita" xtrc="info:3;70:15">
          <codeblock xml:space="preserve" class="+ topic/pre pr-d/codeblock " xtrf="file:/Volumes/Matt_files/Git/mb/markdown-validator/docs-user/user-guide/tasks/t_set-output-format.dita" xtrc="codeblock:5;71:43">md-validate validate docs/ --rules rules/tutorial.json --format csv --output reports/</codeblock>
          <p class="- topic/p " xtrf="file:/Volumes/Matt_files/Git/mb/markdown-validator/docs-user/user-guide/tasks/t_set-output-format.dita" xtrc="p:3;72:14">Each row in the CSV file represents one rule evaluation. Columns
          include the rule ID, name, type, level, and pass/fail status.</p>
          <note type="tip" class="- topic/note " xtrf="file:/Volumes/Matt_files/Git/mb/markdown-validator/docs-user/user-guide/tasks/t_set-output-format.dita" xtrc="note:1;74:28">CSV output is most useful when combined with
          <codeph class="+ topic/ph pr-d/codeph " xtrf="file:/Volumes/Matt_files/Git/mb/markdown-validator/docs-user/user-guide/tasks/t_set-output-format.dita" xtrc="codeph:6;75:19">--output</codeph> to save the file. See
          <xref href="t_save-reports.dita" class="- topic/xref " xtrf="file:/Volumes/Matt_files/Git/mb/markdown-validator/docs-user/user-guide/tasks/t_set-output-format.dita" xtrc="xref:1;76:44" type="task"><?ditaot usertext?>Save validation reports to disk<?ditaot genshortdesc?><desc class="- topic/desc ">Use the <codeph class="+ topic/ph pr-d/codeph " xtrf="file:/Volumes/Matt_files/Git/mb/markdown-validator/docs-user/user-guide/tasks/t_save-reports.dita" xtrc="codeph:1;23:30">--output</codeph> option to write one report file   per validated document to a directory. This is useful for sharing results with   your team, uploading reports as CI artifacts, or tracking quality over time.</desc></xref>.</note>
        </info>
      </step>

    </steps>

  </taskbody>
</task>